The paper deals with network embedding, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) since the paper deals with real-world social networks and digital platforms. The second likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) since the paper proposes a novel multi-view network embedding algorithm that uses graph factorization clustering and co-regularized multi-view agreement. The third likely category is cs.SD (Software Engineering) since the paper discusses practical approaches to problems such as node labeling. The fourth likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) since the paper deals with constructing low-dimensional node embeddings from multi-view networks. The fifth likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval) since the paper discusses the use of network embeddings for labeling unlabeled nodes in the networks.
